<TITLE> Nahid gets death threat over policy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 23 (bdnews24.com)--Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid has received death threat purportedly from Islamists for adopting agnostic education policy. The ministry's public relations officer Subodh Chandra Dhali told reporters on Monday the anonymous letter was sent to the ministry on Nov 18. Legal action will be taken on the matter, he said. Addressing the minister, the letter said: "...Be ready for your death." It also said no-law enforcers could save the enemies of Islam who include independence leader Sheikh Mujibur Rahman's history and adopt irreligious education policy in the curriculum instead of a religion-based one. The sender asked the minister to stop formulating the wrong education policy. "Otherwise another Aug 15 or Aug 21 recur in the country," it threatened. b
